12:
Are you always this dedicated to
your cooking? You select ingredients
with such painstaking attention to
detail.
20:
Why split your attention in that
direction? Are you trying to open a
restaurant?
23:
You seem to have an aversion to
committing to one task. Like your
hesitation to finish off your foes.
25:
Relying on natural talent alone only
gets you so far.
29:
Maybe I like being a jack of all
trades?
You and I really don't have much in
common, do we...
33:
Anyway, if that's all, I've gotta be on
my way.
37: I, too, have something to care of.
43:
Only an imbecile would come
looking to eat dirt a second time. But
I'm curious what you have to say for
yourself first.
46:
Your senses are as sharp as ever,
Shuilong.
47:
I'll cut to the chase: I want to hire
you again.
50:
So you didn't learn a thing from our
last encounter. Let me phrase it
even clearer: you're wasting both
our time.
53:
First the Wicked Witch of the Rift,
now you? What's so interesting
about that boy and his friends
anyway?
54:
You're not allowed to kill, and you're
not making any money off of this
arrangement. Why stick with it?
56:
If you're trying to be a stalker, you're
certainly not doing a very good job.
58:
Is that all? If so, then I'll be taking my
leave.
61:
W-wait! I'll pay however much you
want, just give me information on
your new pals!
64:
Just when I thought you couldn't be
any more pathetic.
69:
We can give you unlimited power!
That's what you truly desire, right?
70:
You'll be unstoppable! Once we
perfect immortality, that can be
yours too!
73:
Oh? So you think that these fists of
mine...
74:
Are inferior to your man-made
abominations?
78:
Looks like you need to be taught a
lesson.
81:
Eep! D-damn it... The rest of you, get
out here!
83:
You should've just listened to my
proposal... But now I know you're too
dangerous to be left alive!
86:
This is all you've got? A half-baked
attempt at a dragon?
91:
Your money would've been better
spent on procuring a real one.
97:
As if I'd ever accept power from you
lot. My fists alone will make me the
most powerful warrior of all time.
101:
Brief as it was, I had a good time
today. But now I've grown tired of
playing with you—
107:
Get out of here while you have the
chance!
116:
I thought you said you honored your
contracts.
119:
I'm starting to think I shouldn't, so
your life could be free for the taking...
131:
But don't think I've accepted your
methods. I still don't know why you
adhere to such stupidity.
134:
That man was one of your
enemies—an evil meant to be
purged. Why did you save him?
136:
What worth is there in preserving
that existence?
140: What if I said it's my policy to do so?
150:
Besides, who says you get decide
how much someone's life is worth?
157: I don't understand you at all.
159:
How can you concentrate in a fight
when your mind is filled with so
much nonsense?
162:
If you really want to know, then you'll
have to start putting yourself in the
shoes of those you've looked down
on.
169:
You are a nuisance. In fact, I despise
you. I am tempted—so incredibly
tempted—to end this contract.
172:
But fine. I'll continue to be in your
employ, until the day you meet a
death worthy of your miserable life.
175:
I'll be expecting your cooking every
day until then.
181:
Hooooly mackerel, I thought I was
done for...
184:
"I despise you, but I'll continue to be
in your employ."
Geez...
188:
Only someone like her could get
away with mouthing off at their boss
like that...
